@nelsonth just feel like I need to jump in here. Not every disabled person has a case as severe as Stephen Hawking. People also consider him ugly btw. 

But people can have a wide range of disabilities and not even know it. They can be physical, intellectual, behavioral/mental (bipolar, chronic depression, PTSD, etc.), or illness related (some can even be completely invisible to the naked eye).

So millions of people who we consider ‚Äúbeautiful‚Äù are also disabled because disability doesn‚Äôt have a specific look. You could be disabled but think you‚Äôre not. Stephen Hawking is not the only way disability exists or presents itself. It‚Äôs important to learn these things - the disability community is the only community that everyone will inevitably be a part of at some point.

